summary: A subpoena issued by the U.S. Attorney's Office for the Southern District of New York to the Massachusetts Registry of Vital Records, commanding the production of a birth certificate for an individual (name redacted) in connection with the criminal case United States v. Ghislaine Maxwell. The subpoena requires the registry's custodian to appear in court on November 29, 2021.

keyFacts: The subpoena seeks a birth certificate for an individual whose name is fully redacted in the document (shown as 'N.' • • -(DOR 1').
This is an official court document from the criminal case United States v. Ghislaine Maxwell (20 Cr. 330 (AJN)).
The subpoena was issued by U.S. Attorney Audrey Strauss on July 19, 2021, with a court appearance scheduled for November 29, 2021.
Failure to comply with the subpoena constitutes contempt of court and may result in civil sanctions and criminal penalties.
The document indicates the prosecution was gathering vital records, possibly to establish the identity or age of a witness or victim.
